[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    344[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mBAA[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;192;197;206m|[38;2;192;197;206m AWS BAA signed. All services in the architecture must be HIPAA-eligible: OpenSearch Service, DynamoDB, Bedrock, Lambda, API Gateway, Kinesis, Firehose, S3, SageMaker, Step Functions, EventBridge, Location Service, KMS are all on the HIPAA Eligible Services list. <!-- TODO: confirm Bedrock + the specific embedding and LLM models you select are eligible at the time of build; verify Location Service eligibility entry; the eligible list has been evolving. --> [38;2;192;197;206m|[K
