[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    383[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mStep 1: Ingest a provider record and validate it before indexing.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m When a provider event arrives (new credentialing record, claims-derived update, NPPES delta), the ingestion pipeline matches the record to existing providers (NPI is the primary key; tax ID and address-similarity are fallbacks for dedupe), validates the data, annotates it with the standardized taxonomy, generates an embedding for the searchable profile text, and only then promotes it into the index. Skip validation and you index garbage; skip embedding and you lose semantic search; skip the staging step and bad records are visible to patients before anyone notices.[K
